trpzPortMib.name: trpzPortMib

revisions.description: v1.2.0: Factored out the 'TrpzPhysPortNumber' textual convention (moved to the new module Basic TC). Added in Basic TC MIB an extension of 'TrpzPhysPortNumber' to permit a value of zero. The new textual convention is 'TrpzPhysPortNumberOrZero'. Using it in this MIB because 'trpzPortConfigTrunkMaster' must be zero for a port that is not part of any port group. This will be published in 7.1 release.
v1.0.1: Fixed imports and compliance group

TrpzPortMode.name: TrpzPortMode
TrpzPortMode.description: Enumeration for the port mode (administratively controlled).

TrpzPortPoeMode.name: TrpzPortPoeMode
TrpzPortPoeMode.description: Enumeration for the port PoE supply configuration: the availability of Power over Ethernet is administratively controlled, can be enabled or disabled. Some ports may not have the Power over Ethernet hardware: they should always appear as disabled.

trpzPortConfigPortMode.name: trpzPortConfigPortMode
trpzPortConfigPortMode.description: Indicates whether this port is configured for directly attached AP, as network port, or for wired auth.

trpzPortConfigPoeMode.name: trpzPortConfigPoeMode
trpzPortConfigPoeMode.description: Indicates whether this port is configured to supply PoE (Power over Ethernet).

trpzPortConfigTrunkMaster.name: trpzPortConfigTrunkMaster
trpzPortConfigTrunkMaster.description: The master port of the group this port belongs to (identified by the physical port number). A zero value means information is not available (usually if this port is not part of any port group).

trpzPortCompliance.name: trpzPortCompliance
trpzPortCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement the Port MIB.

trpzPortConfigGroup.name: trpzPortConfigGroup
trpzPortConfigGroup.description: Mandatory group of objects implemented to provide Port configuration info.
